episodes.title: Swim Shady
episodes.plot: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q hit some bad reception while working a desk, and then head to a park to ask strangers for advice on their questionable life choices. Plus, the loser goes to a water aerobics class, but ends up drowning in shame.

episodes.title: Lady and the Tramp
episodes.plot: Q, Sal, Murr and Joe use a two-way mirror to get each other to crack, and then hit a grocery to see who can sell the most samples. Plus, the loser gets taken for a ride that ends with a visit to the Statue of Liberty.

episodes.title: The Parent Trap
episodes.plot: Sal, Joe, Murr and Q get stuck in a grocery showdown, beg strangers for questionable quotes, and spew financial tips that are anything but sound. Plus, tonight's loser earns a time-out for his outrageous antics at a kid's play space.

episodes.title: Catastrophe
episodes.plot: Murr, Sal, Q and Joe serve up the goods posing as trainees at a juice bar and plead with strangers to get things untangled. Plus, the big loser confronts his biggest fear in a punishment that leaves him practically catatonic.

episodes.title: Vampire Weakened
episodes.plot: Q, Murr, Sal, and Joe pose at employees at an ice cream shop and get strangers to watch their dogs. Plus, tonight's big loser is forced to sink his teeth into an humiliating punishment.

episodes.title: Footloose
episodes.plot: Joe, Murr, Q and Sal call out odd names while working at an office. Later, the guys ask park-goers for help with online dating profiles. And the loser fails to keep his cool while getting up close and personal with some strange feet.

episodes.title: X-Man
episodes.plot: The first ever 4 way challenge sees the jokers compete against each other in a last man standing laughing contest whilst sat in a waiting room. The jokers then have to get members of the public to agree with ridiculous statements.

episodes.title: Medium, Well Done
episodes.plot: Murr, Sal, Q and Joe climb the corporate ladder as TV execs pitching insane show ideas, and the big loser bares his soul while undergoing a humiliating psychic reading that puts his real life on the wrong track.

episodes.title: Drum and Drummer
episodes.plot: Sal, Murr, Q and Joe convince shoppers to repeat bizarre catch phrases, then go mental while psychoanalyzing strangers. Plus, it's an awkward drum roll for the pair of losers when they're forced to perform at a halftime show.

episodes.title: The Butt of the Joker
episodes.plot: Sal, Q, Joe and Murr are partners in focus group presentations, supporting one another's insane ideas on living life to the fullest. And the loser tries to cure the public of a nasty habit - but gets people smoking mad.

episodes.title: Stuffed Turkey
episodes.plot: The jokers act as not-so-handy-men assembling furniture, drop underwear into shopper's bags at the mall, and mistake strangers for someone they know at the supermarket. The loser has to stuff his hands and face while speed dating.

episodes.title: Crickets
episodes.plot: It's hats off for Murr, Sal, Q and Joe when they work as cap salesmen. Then, the guys head to Joey Fatone's hot dog joint to serve confused customers. And the loser performs a stand-up comedy routine but barely gets out alive.

episodes.title: Universal Appeal
episodes.plot: Q, Sal, Murr and Joe invade Orlando. The guys are out of line managing a ride at a theme park, then get all wet on a river adventure, and man the (mis)information booth. Plus, tonight's loser goes from spider hero to barnyard zero.

episodes.title: Paradise Lost
episodes.plot: Sal, Murr, Joe and Q say "aloha'' from Hawaii; blood in the water after the loser with too many fails swims with the fishes.

episodes.title: Mime and Punishment
episodes.plot: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q put the nasty in "namaste" when they lead guided meditations that leave their victims with a lot to think about. And the big loser gets boxed in with the very first 24-hour punishment.

episodes.title: Three Men and Your Baby
episodes.plot: Sal, Joe, Murr and Q get snap happy posing as photographers; three Jokers are faced with a punishment that's not child's play.

episodes.title: The Q-Pay
episodes.plot: Q, Murr, Sal and Joe share some TMI texts with strangers, then try to sabotage each other at a dating event. And tonight's loser gets a special donation from one of the other guys - that he must sport for the rest of the season.

episodes.title: Rubbed the Wrong Way
episodes.plot: Joe, Sal, Q and Murr cruise the food court sending texts to strangers, then throw caution (and groceries) to the wind. And the loser is cast as a genie in a play but wishes he could be anywhere else.

episodes.title: Flatfoot the Pirate
episodes.plot: Q, Sal, Joe and Murr must explain why they've suddenly been doused with water while working at the mall. Plus, the big loser gets decked out as a pirate but won't find any rum in his cup as he entertains kids set on mutiny.

episodes.title: Remember the Pact
episodes.plot: Murr, Sal, Joe and Q beg shoppers to hold on to a weird item for them, then help teach tech to senior citizens. Plus, after a successful secret pact, tonight's loser reveals his embarrassing digital life to his own father.

episodes.title: Silence of the Lame
episodes.plot: It's all play and no work when Sal, Murr, Q and Joe square off in a toy-pitching competition. And tonight's big loser nearly gets the shush beat out of him while trying to quiet down patrons in the food court.

episodes.title: The Walking Dread
episodes.plot: Joe, Murr, Sal and Q take time to smell the roses, while strangers wonder what stinks. Later, the guys pair up to double dip, and tonight's loser goes underground to save his family but ends up battling an undead enemy.

episodes.title: Take Me Out at the Ballgame
episodes.plot: Q, Murr, Joe and Sal get drenched at a water park, then play a wild round of TP basketball at the grocery store. Plus, tonight's loser strikes out while jockeying for a ball from New York Mets pitcher Noah Syndergaard.

episodes.title: The Party Crasher
episodes.plot: Joe, Sal, Q and Murr dodge shakedowns with the help of some strangers, then get handsy in a parking lot. A clip bait battle goes down in the park, and tonight's loser has a run-in at a party that leaves him down for the count.

episodes.title: Dover and Out
episodes.plot: Sal, Murr, Joe and Q survey employees with questions that aren't HR friendly, then get their heads stuck in the clouds. Plus, the loser unveils a spectacular mural in a small town whose residents react with big city rage.

episodes.title: G.I. Jokers
episodes.plot: Sal, Joe, Murr and Q share some (mis)information on aviation, then brag about their lack of accomplishments. Plus, three brave vets get their own permanent punishments, and an epic double punishment goes up in flames.
